      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. So you're essentially saying that Candidate B's background makes them inherently less \"professional\" in a corporate sense? It feels like you're implying that their involvement in things like hip-hop and community work makes them less suited for a structured hierarchy, whereas Candidate A's more traditional, Ivy League background is automatically synonymous with reliability and discipline. Is there a reason why certain cultural markers are being used to predict their work ethic or suitability for the role?",
